posts.title: Post 1
posts.content: Today, healthcare research methodologies are crucial for addressing existing and emerging challenges. To make informed decisions, practitioners, policymakers, and stakeholders use the relevant data and insights provided by these methodologies. The methodologies fall into two broad categories, namely, qualitative and quantitative research. Through analyzing human experiences and behaviors, qualitative research offers a detailed understanding of healthcare problems (Barroga & Matanguihan, 2022). The focus of quantitative research is statistical analyses, identifying patterns, and numerical data.
